	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />On the 3-button controller, &quot;Select&quot; is an output from the console, roughly analogous to $4016 D0 out on an NES or Super NES. It switches the A, B, C, and Start lines between two of the pairs of buttons. On the 6-button controller, it switches more lines if toggled multiple times within a millisecond. (<a href="https://segaretro.org/Six_Button_Control_Pad_(Mega_Drive)#Technical_Information" class="postlink">Source</a>)<br /><br />Your JAMMA harness will need a circuit that toggles Select, latches the output in both states, and relays it to the system board.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


