		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />...In other words, I need to find another solution for a controller. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_neutral.gif" alt=":|" title="Neutral" /> I could make a somewhat-ghetto arcade controller out of wood and screws from Lowes and it would be largely cheaper than any one I could buy, but I kind of want an actual handheld controller with a d-pad. An arcade joystick without a cabinet just feels off to me.<br /><br />I can't believe how expensive some of this stuff is for people who don't know what they're doing. Individual parts, like a power supply or signal converter, are pretty cheap, but once you throw them altogether in a box, it eclipses the cost of the actual arcade pcb. Also, what's the fun in that? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" />

		

